# Coding standards

- Python 3.12, type-hinted throughout; Pydantic v2 DTOs at every API boundary; SQLAlchemy 2 + Alembic
  migrations (never edit the DB schema without a migration).
- FastAPI routers thin; logic in module `service.py`. Dependency-inject via `app/deps.py`.
- Long-running work (research runs, backtests, evolution) goes to Celery workers, never the request path.
- Determinism: seed randomness in backtests/Monte Carlo; pin model + data versions in provenance so
  results are reproducible.
- Tests are part of every milestone (see docs/06). Use pytest; include the harness verification suite and
  the safety drills. A milestone is not done until its acceptance gate tests pass.
- Frontend: React 18 + TS + Vite, Tailwind + shadcn/ui, TanStack Query for server state. Every data view
  implements empty / loading / partial / error / alert states. Round all displayed numbers.
- No secrets in code or client bundles. Config via pydantic-settings/env. Keep functions small and the
  module's public surface minimal.
- Match the file tree in docs/02 exactly; if a path is ambiguous, prefer the doc over improvisation.

- Theming: all colors resolve through CSS variables driven by a `data-theme` root attribute (system/light/dark).
  Never hardcode colors in components. Theme is a persisted user preference (Settings → Appearance), default system,
  applied before first paint. Tokens and the signature confidence-bar component are specified in docs/10.
